). Podonotum with 20 pairs of setae, j 1-6 , z 2-6 , s 1-6 , r 2 and r 4-5 inserted dorsally, r 1 and r 3 inserted ventrally, on peritrematal shields. Podonotal setae j 1 , z 3 , s 2-3 , r 2 , r 4-5 and s 6 densely plumose, brush-like, other setae on the shield short, smooth and needle-like. Glands
